-- Zuma's Nephew, Dongfeng to Sell Cars in South Africa, Business Report Says
-- Franz Wild
-- 2010-07-21T06:52:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/zuma-s-nephew-dongfeng-to-sell-cars-in-south-africa-business-report-says.html

          
          
             South African President  Jacob Zuma ’s
nephew and Dongfeng Motor Group started a venture to sell the
Chinese government-owned company’s cars in South Africa,
 Business Report  said.  
 The venture between Khulubuse Zuma and Dongfeng will start
selling cars by the end of the year, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said, citing Zuma. The companies will later assemble
cars in South Africa and aims to expand sales into the rest of
the continent, Business Report said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
